http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Man-held-on-the-charge-of-sexually-assaulting-sister-in-law/article13977764.ece

The police arrested a person on the charge of threatening and raping his sister-in-law at Kukkundur in Karkala on January 1.The police said that the accused was a resident of Kukkundur, Karkala. He used to go to his father-in-law’s house and used to sexually assault his sister-in-law, aged 55, despite her and her father’s protests.He used to threaten both of them. This was going on for quite some time. Finally, the victim’s father lodged a complaint with the police on December 31.A case was registered under Sections 376 (rape) and 506 (criminal intimidation) of Indian Penal Code at the Karkala Town Police Station. The police arrested him on January 1, and produced him before a court in Karkala, which remanded him in judicial custody for two weeks, the police said.